Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
saveRouteGuide(25.10)                                    saveRouteGuide(25.10)

Name
       saveRouteGuide  - Saves the routing information to a route guide format
       file

Syntax
       saveRouteGuide

       [-help]

       [-rguide <routeGuideFileName>]

       [-selNetFile <selNetFileName>]

       Saves the routing information to a route  guide  format  file.  Routing
       guide  files  help  control the routing topology by creating regions in
       which Early Global Route can create  wires.  You  can  use  the  saveR-
       outeGuide  command  after running Early Global Route or after restoring
       routing data.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each saveRouteGuide parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command

              man saveRouteGuide.

       -rguide <routeGuideFileName>
              Specifies  the route guide file to which to save the routing in-
              formation.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -selNetFile <selNetFileName>
              Specifies a file of hierarchical net names  for  which  to  save
              route  information.  Routing information is saved only for these
              nets.

              Data_type: string, optional

Examples
              * The following command writes the route  information  in  route
                guide format to the cts_3.guide file:

                saveRouteGuide -rguide cts_3.guide

Related Information
              * earlyGlobalRoute

              * Using  Early  Global  Route for Congestion and Timing Analysis
                chapter in the Innovus User Guide

